<div class="calcpad-output">
 <!-- Solves $x^x = 10$ with Newton iteration and renders an animated SVG that highlights each tangent step.
<p>The frame loop turns convergence into a visual sequence rather than a printed iteration table. -->
 <p>
  <strong>Problem:</strong>
  Given the following equation:
  <span class="eq">
   <var>x</var>
   <sup>
    <var>x</var>
   </sup>
   = 10
  </span>
  . Find
  <span class="eq">
   <var>x</var>
  </span>
  = ?
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
 <p>
  <strong>Solution:</strong>
  Transform the equation in the form:
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  =
   <var>x</var>
   <sup>
    <var>x</var>
   </sup>
   − 10
  </span>
  = 0
 </p>
 <p>
  The first derivative is
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f′</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  =
   <var>x</var>
   <sup>
    <var>x</var>
   </sup>
   ·  (
   <b>ln</b>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  + 1 )
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Initial guess -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>x</var>
   <sub>0</sub>
   = 4
  </span>
  , target precision -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>δ</var>
   = 10
   <sup>-14</sup>
  </span>
 </p>
